nded}}\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Francis Crick Institute}}\n{{League of European Research Universities}}\n{{Global Alliance of Technological Universities}}\n{{Russell Group}}\n{{Universities and colleges in London}}\n{{Universities in the United Kingdom}}\n{{University of London}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Imperial College London| ]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1907]]\n[[Category:Former colleges of the University of London]]\n[[Category:Russell Group]]\n[[Category:1907 establishments in England]] \n[[Category:South Kensington]]\n[[Category:Universities in London]]\n", "name_user": "Shadowssettle", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCampuses:up-to-date image post Exhibition Road referb", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imperial_College_London"}
{"title_page": "List of train surfing injuries and deaths", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n[[File:ER2-1274 Backride 2.jpg|thumb|[[Sokolovskaya (railway station)|Sokolovskaya]], 2011]]\nThis is a list of '''injuries and deaths''' during [[train surfing]].\n\nCommon ways that injuries and deaths from train surfing may occur include being electrocuted from overhead power lines, falling off and falling underneath the wheels of the train.<ref name=Damane2015 >{{Cite news\n  |url=https://www.groundup.org.za/article/riders-trains_2821/\n  |title=Riders of the Trains\n  |last=Damane  |first=Mosa\n  |date=9 April 2015\n  |work=GroundUp\n  |access-date=8 January 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n===Australia===\nIt has been reported that during the period from 2010 to 2014 there were 479 overall incidents of train surfing on railways in Melbourne.<ref name=9news2015>{{Cite news|url=https://www.9news.com.au/national/melbourne-man-clings-to-life-after-jumping-from-a-moving-train/c36b53a5-5b5c-4c6c-b3d5-1d47270d25ab|title=Melbourne man clings to life after jumping from a moving train|date=26 February 2015|work=9news|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref> It has also been reported that the number of people who were caught train surfing in 2011 was 333, while in 2010 there was a total of 294 who were caught.<ref name=10newsJan2012>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0oyb97ed6vw|title=Train tragedy|date=24 January 2012|work=10news|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref> Between July 2019 and March 2020 46 arrests were made for train surfing on trains in Sydney.<ref name=9newsJan2012>{{Cite news|url=https://www.9news.com.au/national/sydney-news-teenager-captured-on-camera-hanging-off-back-of-train/2de6708a-af51-45ea-a377-de43aee78ddc|title=Teen filmed risking life on back of train|date=20 March 2019|work=9news|access-date=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Brazil - Rio de Janeiro===\nIt was written in a study published in the Journal \"Burns\" in August 2000, that \"train surfers\" is a term that describes \"adolescents from the outskirts of the city of Rio de Janeiro, who are compelled by the overcrowded railway trains to travel on the roofs of the wagons\" and that there had been \"over 100 fatalities in more than 200 registered accidents over the past 10 years.\"<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sternick|first=I.|last2=Gomes|first2=R.D.|last3=Radwanski|first3=H.N.|last4=Pitanguy|first4=I.|date=August 2000|title=\"Train surfers\": analysis of 23 cases of electrical burns caused by high tension railway overhead cables|journal=Burns : Journal of the International Society for Burn Injuries|volume=26|issue=5|pages=470\u2013473|doi=10.1016/S0305-4179(99)00173-4|pmid=10812270|issn=0305-4179}}</ref>\n\n===Germany===\nIn Germany between 1989 and 1995 there were 41 train surfing accidents. 18 of these 41 accidents resulted in the person's death.The age range of the people involved in the accidents was from 13 to 25 and in over 50% of the cases alcohol was a factor involved.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Strauch|first=H.|last2=Wirth|first2=I.|last3=Geserick|first3=I.|date=8 June 1998|title=Fatal accidents due to train surfing in Berlin|journal=Forensic Science International|volume=94|issue=1\u20132|pages=119\u2013127|doi=10.1016/S0379-0738(98)00064-4|pmid=9670490|issn=0379-0738}}</ref> It was reported that in 2008 40 people died due to train surfing in Germany.<ref name=\"SurferToday What is train surfing?\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.surfertoday.com/surfing/what-is-train-surfing|title=What is train surfing?|work=Surfer Today|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref> A train surfing incident occurred in Frankfurt in 2019. At the time a news source quoted a person in Frankfurt as saying that \"...there have been hardly any such cases since the late 1990s. At that time, the police in Germany often had to deal with... S-Bahn surfers.\" <ref name=Rosendorff2019>{{Cite news|url=https://www.fr.de/frankfurt/frankfurt-am-main-ort28687/frankfurt-s-bahn-surfer-steht-brennend-bahn-polizei-sichtet-videos-zr-13027323.html|title=Man burns on S-Bahn - police evaluate video footage|last=Rosendorff|first=Kathrin|date=24 September 2019|work=Frankfurter Rundschau|access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Indonesia===\nIn a 2012 news report from ODN it said that \"According to statistics riding on the roofs of trains killed 11 people in Indonesia last year.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YuCMm7F08ik|title=Stone balls to knock passengers off Indonesian train roofs|last=Datta-Paulin|first=Sam|date=26 January 2012|work=ODN|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Russia===\nIt was reported that \"In 2011, over 100 train surfers died in Russia.\"<ref name=\"SurferToday What is train surfing?\" /> It was reported that the injury and death counts for incidents on railways in Russia in 2015 include \"25 children and teenagers, many of whom suffered accidents while trying to ride outside train cars or to make a selfie\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2015/08/04/another-russian-teenager-dies-while-trying-to-take-a-selfie-on-a-train-a48723|title=Another Russian Teenager Dies While Trying to Take a Selfie on a Train|last=Doglov|first=Anna|date=4 August 2015|work=The Moscow Times|access-date=23 January 2020}}</ref>In 2016 30 minors were injured while train surfing and seven of these people were killed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ria.ru/20170518/1494572825.html?in=t|title=Ministry of Internal Affairs: every fifth teenager injured in railway traffic fell from the roof of the train|date=18 May 2017|work=RIA Novosti|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> Also in 2016 1,000 people were arrested for train surfing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/le-train-surfing-cette-pratique-inconsciente-qui-a-tue-sur-le-metro-a-paris-25-10-2017-7354173.php|title=\u201cTrain-surfing\u201d, this unconscious practice that killed on the metro in Paris|first=Romain|last=Baheux|date=25 October 2017|work=Le Parisien|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> In the six months to July 2017 there were 21 people who were killed and another 45 people injured whilst train surfing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jVX-gk3MF7k|title=Investigative Committee releases data on the death of teenage hookers - 21 people were killed in six months|date=26 July 2017|work=ORT|access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://rtd.rt.com/stories/train-surfing-russian-thrill-seekers/|title=Train Surfing: Russian thrill-seekers risk life and limb for the sensation of flight|date=16 April 2019|work=RT Documentary|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===South Africa===\nIt has been reported that across the [[Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa|PRASA network]] in 2013, there was a total of 238 fatalities, of which 17 of these were due to train surfing.<ref name=Damane2015 />\n\n===Ukraine - Kiev===\nIt was reported that \"in May 2018, the website of the National Police of Kiev announced that it had \"caught\" 12 juvenile hookers in the subway.\"<ref name=newsmir18march2019>{{Cite news|url=https://newsmir.info/1616487|title=The teenager was on the verge of death in Kiev: a terrible incident hit the camera|date=18 March 2019|work=Newsmir|access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===United States - New York===\nIt has been reported that \"Subway surfing was a form of thrill-seeking in the late 1980s and early '90s when several teenagers lost their lives.\" <ref name=Onishi >{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/07/15/nyregion/youth-is-killed-riding-on-roof-of-subway-car-in-the-bronx.html|title=Youth Is Killed Riding on Roof Of Subway Car In the Bronx|last=Onishi|first=Norimitsu|date=15 July 1996|work=The New York Times|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Train surfing injuries and deaths ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Date\n! scope=\"col\" |Location\n! scope=\"col\" |Died/\nInjured\n! scope=\"col\" |Type\n! scope=\"col\" |Ages\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |Description\n\n|-\n|{{dts|31 May 1994}}\n|United States - New York\n|Died\n|Hit by object\n|19\n|A 19-year-old was riding on top of a train with another person when it entered a tunnel. It is thought that when the train moved from elevated tracks into a tunnel, the 19 year-old hit the entrance to the tunnel and was killed. His body was found just north of the 149th street station.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/05/31/nyregion/man-dies-in-train-tunnel.html|title=Man Dies in Train Tunnel|date=31 May 1994|work=The New York Times|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|{{dts|15 July 1996}}\n|United States - New York\n|Died\n|Hit by object\n|?\n|A person was riding on top of a train carriage when they hit a signal light, were thrown on to the tracks and killed. The death happened close to the [[Bronx Park East station]] in [[Pelham Parkway]]. A news report estimated their age as between 16 and 20 years old.\n<ref name=Onishi />\n\n|-\n|{{dts|}}\n|Germany\n|Died\n|Hit by object\n|22\n|A person, 22, was killed whilst train surfing. They were on top of a train and collided with a signal mast.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vice.com/de/article/nzn49k/ein-lokfuehrer-erzaehlt-so-fuehlt-es-sich-an-einen-menschen-zu-ueberfahren|title=A train driver says: This is what it feels like to run over a person|last=Ramlow|first=Rebecca|date=12 December 2016|work=Vice in German|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|{{dts|5 November 2002}}\n|United Kingdom - East Sussex\n|Died\n|Hit by object\n|18\n|An 18-year-old was killed after [[Guy Fawkes night]] celebrations in [[East Sussex]]. They climbed out of the window of the train and up onto the roof. It is thought that he was killed when the train traveled over a bridge and part of the bridge hit the 18-year-old. A friend who was with the 18-year-old at the time alerted the train driver using the emergency cord and the driver stopped the train at the next station.\n<ref>{{Cite news\n  |url=https://www.sussexexpress.co.uk/news/youth-s-tragic-rail-death-1-957453\n  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180424135340/https://www.sussexexpress.co.uk/news/youth-s-tragic-rail-death-1-957453\n  |url-status=dead\n  |archive-date=24 April 2018\n  |title=Youth's tragic rail death|date=7 November 2002|work=[[Sussex Express]]|access-date=6 January 2020\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news\n  |url=https://www.vice.com/en_ca/article/mbxn5p/the-teens-risking-their-lives-to-surf-on-trains-and-buses|title=The Teens Risking Their Lives to 'Surf' On Trains and Buses|date=24 April 2018|work=VICE Canada|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|{{dts|20 October 2003}}\n|United States - New York\n|Died\n|Hit by Object\n|14\n|A 14-year-old, and 10 people from their high school got on a train at the [[14th Street/Eighth Avenue station|14th Street and Eighth Avenue station]]. The 14-year-old was riding between two carriages using a safety chain to rock back and forth. He handed his hat, jersey, necklace and book bag to the other people there. The 14-year-old then said that they wanted to lie down on the top of the roof and began to climb up. At the top of the train he wedged his legs in between two carriages, was hit by a trackside beam, thrown onto the tracks by the impact and was then hit by the rear carriages of the train. They were killed as a result of the incident.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2003/10/22/subway-pals-horror-surfing-teen-died-as-she-clung-to-him/|title=SUBWAY PAL'S HORROR: 'SURFING' TEEN DIED AS SHE CLUNG TO HIM|date=22 October 2003|last=Mcgurk|first=Joe|work=Ny Post|access-date=11 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/10/21/nyregion/14-year-old-killed-in-stunt-atop-a-subway-train.html|title=14-Year-Old Killed in Stunt Atop a Subway Train|date=21 October 2003|last=Lueck|first=Thomas J|last2=Piazza|first2=Jo|work= NY Post|access-date=11 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gothamist.com/news/teen-dies-while-trying-to-subway-surf|title=Teen Dies While Trying to \"Subway Surf\"|date=21 October 2003|last=Chung|first=Jen|work=Gothamist|access-date=11 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111050505/https://gothamist.com/news/teen-dies-while-trying-to-subway-surf|archive-date=11 January 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|{{dts|14 November 2003}}\n|United States - New York\n|Died\n|Hit by Object\n|22 21\n|A 22-year-old and a 21-year-old, were with two other people at [[Bleecker Street station]], [[Greenwich Village]], when they boarded a train. The 21- and 22 year-old climbed on top of the roof of the train. As the train drove onto the Whitlock bridge they collided with a beam. The 21-year-old was found between the 9th and 10th cars of the train. The 22-year-old died from his injuries on the day of the collision while the 21-year-old was pronounced dead in hospital 6 days later.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2003/11/15/train-surf-horror-cadet-dies-another-hurt-in-subway-stunt/|title=TRAIN-SURF HORROR; CADET DIES, ANOTHER HURT IN SUBWAY STUNT|last=Weiss|first=Murray|date=15 November 2013|work=Ny Post|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/11/21/nyregion/metro-briefing-new-york-bronx-another-death-in-subway-surfing.html?searchResultPosition=2|title=Metro Briefing New York: Bronx: Another Death In Subway Surfing|last=Stevenson|first=Jed|date=21 November 2013|work=New York Times|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/11/16/nyregion/subway-surfing-cadet-in-critical-condition.html?searchResultPosition=3|title=Subway-Surfing Cadet in Critical Condition|date=16 November 2013|work=New York Times|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|{{dts| 2004}}\n|South Africa\n|Injured\n|Electrocuted\n|15\n|A 15-year-old, climbed on top of a train carriage and prepared himself for a train surfing manoeuvre called \"the matrix\". He was then electrocuted by the overhead power lines. The injuries he received include loss of the use of his right hand, loss of his two front teeth and two broken ribs.\n<ref name=Damane2015 />\n\n|-\n|{{dts|2007}}\n|South Africa\n|Injured\n|Electrocuted\n|?\n|In the 2013 mini documentary, \"Staff Riding\" a person is filmed saying that they were holding onto an electric cab cable, and then after that they woke up down at the station.<ref name=Casino2014>{{Cite news|url=https://vimeo.com/83486021|title=Staff Riding|last=Casino|first=Marco|date=2014|work=Marco Casino|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref> They had been on top of a train when they touched the overhead cab cable. They had amputations performed on both arms and one leg following the incidence of electrocution.\n<ref name=Casino2014 /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.marcocasino.com/portfolios/staff-riding/|title=Staff Riding|last=Casino|first=Marco|date=2013|work=Marco Casino|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/2014/05/train-surfing/|title=The Crazy Train Surfers Who Flirt With Death for Sport|last=Seibel|first=Brendan|date=1 May 2014|work=Wired|access-date=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|{{dts|12 May 2007}}\n|Denmark - Midtjylland - Ringk\u00f8bing\n|Died\n|Hit by object\n|22\n|A 22-year-old had been at a football game in Herning and was travelling with three friends to [[Ringkobing]]. The 22-year-old was riding on the top of the train when it travelled through a viaduct near [[Skraldhedevejhe]]. The 22-year-old hit the edge of the viaduct. Their body was noticed lying on top of the train, by motorists.\n<ref>{{Cite news\n  |url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/article.php/id-6950075.html%2529%25252C|title=Dead train surfers known from networks and TV|date=13 May 2007|work=TV2|access-date=10 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.avisen.dk/rest-in-peace-martin_70951.aspx|title=Rest in peace, Martin|last=Malacinski|first=Leny|date=13 May 2007|work=Avisen.dk|acce