ne|last=Schulz|first=Matthew|date=24 January 2011|work=Herald Sun|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|14 February 2011}}\n|Russia - Moscow\n|Died\n|Hit by Object\n|19 19\n|Two 19-year-olds were killed after riding on the roof of a train on the [[Moscow Metro]]. It is thought the two wanted to ride several stations of the [[Filyovskaya line]] which has stations located outside. As well as the outdoor stations the line has underground stations. The two climbed on top of the roof of a train and it is thought they were killed when they were hit by the entrance to a tunnel. One of the two 19-year-old's body was found on the roof of a train at {{stnlnk|Kiyevskaya|Filyovskaya line}} with a skull fracture.  The other 19-year-old's body was found between {{stnlnk|Kuntsevskaya|Moscow Metro}} and {{stnlnk|Pionerskaya|Moscow Metro|Pioneer}} stations with fractures to the bones in his neck. They were found with clothing to assist them in riding the outside of the train including ski masks and gloves.\n<ref>{{Cite news\n  |url=https://www.pravdareport.com/hotspots/116907-train_surfing/|title=Train surfers die horrible death in Moscow metro\n|last=Sudakov|first=Dmitry|date=15 February 2011|work=Pravda|access-date=11 January 2020\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news\n  |url=http://www.metronews.ru/moskva/dvoe-studentov-pogibli-na-kryshe-poezda/Tpokbn---fh1EjKNaLNM62/|title=Two students died on the roof of the train|last=Karpova|first=Ruslana|date=14 February 2011|work=Metro Russia|access-date=11 January 2020\n|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109142920/http://www.metronews.ru/moskva/dvoe-studentov-pogibli-na-kryshe-poezda/Tpokbn---fh1EjKNaLNM62/|archive-date=9 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news\n  |url=https://news.am/eng/news/47874.html|title=Students who died a terrible death in Moscow were Armenian|date=14 February 2011|work=NEWSam|access-date=11 January 2020\n}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|5 September 2011}}\n|United States - Colorado - Longmont\n|Injured\n|Fall\n|17\n|Anna Beninati, 17, was with three friends in Longmont Colorado, planning to hop on board a freight train that would take them back to Colorado State University. They were intending to run alongside the train as it was moving, grab a hold of it and climb on. Beninati has given a description of the incident, ''\"I managed to grab on with my arms ... but my legs didn't make it up onto the train. Instead, they bounced underneath it and dragged against the tracks until they weren't legs anymore. The driver never even knew he had hit me until long afterward. I was conscious the whole time. I got to see my detached limbs lying next to me on the pavement. I clearly remember being lifted onto the stretcher in three distinct pieces...\"''.<ref name=Beninati2015>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cracked.com/personal-experiences-1786-6-things-you-learn-losing-both-your-legs-to-train.html|title=Amputee Fetishes: 6 Realities Of Losing Both Legs As A Girl|last1=Beninati|first1=Anna|last2=Evans|first2=Robert|date=30 June 2015|work=Cracked|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref> Beninati lost her left leg from above the knee and her right leg from below the knee.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.denverpost.com/2011/09/06/calm-aid-givers-reassure-teen-maimed-in-longmont-train-accident-who-asked-am-i-going-to-die/|title=Calm aid-givers reassure teen maimed in Longmont train accident, who asked: \"Am I going to die?\"|date=2 August 2016|work=Denver Post|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/anna-beninati-teen-who-lo_n_1223263|title=Anna Beninati, CSU Teen Who Lost Legs In Longmont Train Accident, Thanks Rescuers At Fire Awards Ceremony (VIDEO)|date=6 December 2017|work=Huff Post|access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=Beninati2015 />\n\n|-\n|{{dts|24 January 2012}}\n|Australia - Melbourne\n|Died\n|Electrocuted \n|17\n|A 17-year-old was with five friends at a train a station intending to travel back to their home. At about 11:00 pm, he was on