{"title_page": "Sjur Jarle Hauge", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian footballer and manager}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Sjur Jarle Hauge\n| image               =\n| fullname            =\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1971|12|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Norway]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.80|precision=0}}\n| clubnumber          =\n| position            = Midfielder\n| youthyears1 =           \n| youthclubs1 =           \n|  years1 =                  \n| years2 =   \n| years3 =  1995\u20131999 \n| years4 =  2000\u20132006 \n| years5 =  2007\u201320??\n|  clubs1 = [[SK Haugar|Haugar]] \n| clubs2 =  [[Bryne FK|Bryne]] \n| clubs3 =  [[FK Haugesund|Haugesund]] \n| clubs4 =  [[Torvastad IL|Torvastad]] \n| clubs5 =  [[SK Djerv 1919|Djerv 1919]]\n| caps1 =            \n| goals1 = \n|  manageryears1 =          2000\u20132006 \n| manageryears2 =  2007\u201320??\n|  managerclubs1 =          [[Torvastad IL|Torvastad]] (player-manager) \n| managerclubs2 =  [[SK Djerv 1919|Djerv 1919]] (player-manager)\n}}\n\n'''Sjur Jarle Hauge''' (born 18 December 1971) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] football coach and former player.\n\nHe started his career in [[SK Haugar]]; and later went to [[Bryne FK|Bryne]]. He joined [[FK Haugesund]] in 1995,<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070811220814/http://www.vg.no/vg/sport/fotball/elfot97/haugst97.htm FK Haugesund squad list 1997] - ''[[Verdens Gang]]''</ref> and enjoyed a spell in the [[Norwegian Premier League]] in the seasons [[Norwegian Premier League 1997|1997]] and [[Norwegian Premier League 1998|1998]].<ref>[http://fotball.bt.no/eliteserien/index.jsp?service=default&stats=true&type=person&personId=2927&seasonId=154 Sjur Jarle Hauge] Norwegian Premier League stats</ref> He left ahead of the 2000 season to become player-coach at [[Torvastad IL]]. In 2007, he was hired in the same position at [[Djerv 1919]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.haugesunds-avis.no/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20070402/SPORT/104020015|title=Vellykket vinter|last=H\u00f8lleland|first=Magne|date=2 April 2007|work=Haugesunds Avis|language=Norwegian|accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hauge, Sjur Jarle}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Haugesund]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:SK Haugar players]]\n[[Category:Bryne FK players]]\n[[Category:FK Haugesund players]]\n[[Category:SK Djerv 1919 players]]\n[[Category:Norwegian football managers]]\n\n{{Norway-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Sjur Jarle Hauge\n| image               =\n| fullname            =\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1971|12|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Norway]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.80|precision=0}}\n| clubnumber          =\n| position            = Midfielder\n| youthyears1 =           \n| youthclubs1 =           \n|  years1 =                  \n| years2 =   \n| years3 =  1995\u20131999 \n| years4 =  2000\u20132006 \n| years5 =  2007\u201320??\n|  clubs1 = [[SK Haugar|Haugar]] \n| clubs2 =  [[Bryne FK|Bryne]] \n| clubs3 =  [[FK Haugesund|Haugesund]] \n| clubs4 =  [[Torvastad IL|Torvastad]] \n| clubs5 =  [[SK Djerv 1919|Djerv 1919]]\n| caps1 =            \n| goals1 = \n|  manageryears1 =          2000\u20132006 \n| manageryears2 =  2007\u201320??\n|  managerclubs1 =          [[Torvastad IL|Torvastad]] (player-manager) \n| managerclubs2 =  [[SK Djerv 1919|Djerv 1919]] (player-manager)\n}}\n\n'''Sjur Jarle Hauge''' (born 18 December 1971) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] football coach and former player.\n\nHe started his career in [[SK Haugar]]; and later went to [[Bryne FK|Bryne]]. He joined [[FK Haugesund]] in 1995,<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070811220814/http://www.vg.no/vg/sport/fotball/elfot97/haugst97.htm FK Haugesund squad list 1997] - ''[[Verdens Gang]]''</ref> and enjoyed a spell in the [[Norwegian Premier League]] in the seasons [[Norwegian Premier League 1997|1997]] and [[Norwegian Premier League 1998|1998]].<ref>[http://fotball.bt.no/eliteserien/index.jsp?service=default&stats=true&type=person&personId=2927&seasonId=154 Sjur Jarle Hauge] Norwegian Premier League stats</ref> He left ahead of the 2000 season to become player-coach at [[Torvastad IL]]. In 2007, he was hired in the same position at [[Djerv 1919]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.haugesunds-avis.no/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20070402/SPORT/104020015|title=Vellykket vinter|last=H\u00f8lleland|first=Magne|date=2 April 2007|work=Haugesunds Avis|language=Norwegian|accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hauge, Sjur Jarle}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Haugesund]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:SK Haugar players]]\n[[Category:Bryne FK players]]\n[[Category:FK Haugesund players]]\n[[Category:SK Djerv 1919 players]]\n[[Category:Norwegian football managers]]\n\n{{Norway-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Norwegian footballer and manager\", overriding Wikidata description \"Norwegian footballer and manager\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sjur_Jarle_Hauge"}
